node.text:
Honored to win this years Triple Crown, it was a ton of fun. I wasn’t sure what to expect when I signed up, I just thought I’d be surfing those spots anyways so I might as well give it a go. Then watching everyone pushing their limits on day 1 got me really inspired, and totally changed my mindset. Big days at Haleiwa, Sunset and Pipe are so taxing, but everyone was putting in a ton of effort and time at each venue. The format was a lot of fun and so unique to what we’re used to. It was wild spending so many hours in the water through all the swell we had. Thank you to the community here on the North Shore for sharing the lineups and making this possible. Congrats @rissmoore10 for winning the women’s division, you were ripping!
-
🎶 @ronartisii

node.text:
After injuring my knee last summer I didn’t think it would be possible to surf the Pipe Masters five months after surgery, but I decided to make that my goal and give myself every chance to compete in case there was still a possibility to qualify for the Olympics.  Hopefully this film inspires people to go after their goals.
	⁃	
Thank you to the medical team and physical therapists that made this possible, to my team for their support over the last year, the team @clifbar for supporting me to tell this story, the @wsl for working with us, and every surfer on tour - it’s incredible to see how far everyone is taking the level of surfing in competition. 
	⁃	
#TokyoRising available on @amazonprimevideo Thursday 11/12
🎥 @parallelsea

node.text: Yesterday was 9 weeks from my ACL surgery, it has been a lot of hard work I am thankful for all the support around me. I can’t wait to compete in the Tokyo Olympics with @teamusa let’s goooo

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by John john Florence on July 12, 2021. May be an image of nature and ocean.

node.text:
This photo brings back some great memories from my last trip to Japan back in 2011.  Hopefully the surf looks like this for the @olympics !  I’m very proud to be representing @usasurfing with @koloheandino22 @rissmoore10 @caroline_markss
-
📸 @lawrence_photo

node.text:
It’s been a fun challenge starting @florence_marine_x from scratch. If you ask our team I probably ask too many questions and give too much input on products hahah, but that’s kind of the fun part for me and why I was motivated to start this brand. 

Boardshorts were the first thing we worked on, and probably the thing I tested and changed the most. We tried to challenge everything from where to source fabrics down to which thread to use in the seams. I’m really stoked on our first line. For me they have worked great surfing and with any kind of water activity. Excited to keep improving them designing more options 🤙

node.text:
I’m pretty sure that anyone who travels with boards has a questionable relationship with the baggage fees. It might be something we all bond over as surfers 😂. 

If you’re traveling with gear this summer I’m partnering with @michelobultra to help cover your oversized baggage fees. Share a photo of your boardbags or gear with @michelobultra #BoardYourGear #sweepstakes for a chance to fly without fees.

node.text:
The support I’ve had this last month has been incredible. Thank you to everyone who has helped me through this recovery process.  It feels so good to be back in the water surfing again!
-
I want to do a giveaway this week around that same idea. I would love to hear about someone who supported you or helped you with something  - it could be anything. Post about the experience and use #getoutthereandlearn - pick any one of my sponsors and I’ll work with them to send a gift to you and the person who gave you that support.  Look forward to seeing what everyone comes up with.  I’ll choose a few of my favorites over the next few days

node.text: Thankful to be feeling stronger every day. It’s been another good learning experience to pay more attention to nutrition and what I put in my body. I recently started working with the team @thornehealth to customize a program that focuses on recovering faster.  I love working with products I believe in. If you want to take a look at what I’m using during this recovery stage check out the link in my bio.
